HEADWORD: Outloose
<hw>Out"loose`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A loosing from; an
escape; an outlet; an evasion.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That ⟦ldquo⟧whereas⟦rdquo⟧ gives me an <qex>outloose</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Selden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Outlope</ent>⟦br⟧
